import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['life_expect', 'fertility']]
    sns.scatterplot(x='fertility', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['life_expect'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Count')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.barplot(x='country', y='pop', data=data, color='blue')

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
